# SirajOS Architecture Freeze v1.0

**Status:** Frozen
**Purpose:** Architectural baseline before refactoring and feature completion.

---

# Goal

The objective of this freeze is to prevent architectural drift while SirajOS is completed.

From this point forward:

* No new architectural patterns.
* No duplicate models.
* No duplicate pipelines.
* No duplicate graph implementations.
* No parallel object hierarchies.

All future work must move toward a single coherent architecture.

---

# Core Layers

The project shall consist of the following layers only.

```
src/

application/
domain/
infrastructure/
core/
cli/
tests/
```

No additional architectural layers are allowed.

---

# Domain Layer

The Domain layer is the source of truth.

Only the Domain layer owns:

* Person
* Location
* Event
* Claim
* Relationship
* Source
* Statistic
* TimelineEvent
* KnowledgeGraph
* KnowledgeNode
* KnowledgeEdge

No copies of these classes may exist elsewhere.

---

# Application Layer

Responsible only for orchestration.

Allowed responsibilities:

* Extraction pipeline
* Documentary generation
* Workflow
* Prompt generation
* Scene planning
* Script generation
* Knowledge organization

The Application layer must never redefine domain objects.

---

# Infrastructure Layer

Responsible for external systems only.

Examples:

* Gemini
* OpenAI
* Storage
* Vector databases
* JSON
* Filesystem
* APIs

Infrastructure must depend on interfaces, never on business logic.

---

# Core Layer

Contains only shared utilities.

Allowed:

* KnowledgeAsset
* Shared abstractions
* Generic helpers

Core must not become another business layer.

---

# Single Source of Truth

The following objects must exist exactly once.

* Claim
* Person
* Event
* Relationship
* Source
* TimelineEvent
* DocumentaryOutline
* Script
* Prompt
* KnowledgeGraph
* EntityResolver
* MergeRules
* Canonicalizer

Duplicate implementations must be eliminated.

---

# Knowledge Pipeline

The canonical pipeline becomes:

```
Document
        │
        ▼
Parser
        │
        ▼
Chunk Builder
        │
        ▼
Extractors
        │
        ▼
Canonicalization
        │
        ▼
Resolution
        │
        ▼
Graph Builder
        │
        ▼
Graph Normalization
        │
        ▼
Quality Engine
        │
        ▼
Knowledge Graph
```

No alternative pipeline is permitted.

---

# Knowledge Graph

Only one implementation exists.

```
KnowledgeGraph
KnowledgeNode
KnowledgeEdge
GraphIndex
GraphResolver
KnowledgeGraphQuery
```

Any application-side graph implementation is temporary and must be removed.

---

# LLM Layer

Only one gateway abstraction.

```
LLMGateway
```

Providers:

* GeminiGateway
* OpenAIGateway
* ManualGateway
* FakeGateway

No additional gateway hierarchy.

---

# Documentary Pipeline

Canonical flow:

```
Knowledge Graph
        │
        ▼
Knowledge Organizer
        │
        ▼
Narrative Builder
        │
        ▼
Outline Builder
        │
        ▼
Scene Planner
        │
        ▼
Prompt Builder
        │
        ▼
Image Generator
        │
        ▼
Script Generator
```

---

# Naming Rules

Every domain object:

* singular
* descriptive
* immutable when possible

Avoid names like:

* V2
* New
* Final
* Copy
* Temp

---

# Dependency Rules

Allowed direction:

```
Infrastructure
        ↓
Application
        ↓
Domain
```

Never:

* Domain → Infrastructure
* Domain → Application

---

# Testing Rules

Tests must target canonical classes only.

Any test referencing deprecated models must be migrated or removed.

---

# Deprecation Policy

The following folders are considered transitional and must disappear before v1.

* application/models duplication
* application/knowledge_v2 duplication
* legacy graph implementations
* duplicate resolver implementations
* duplicate normalizers

---

# Refactoring Policy

Every architectural change must satisfy all of the following:

1. Reduce duplication.
2. Increase cohesion.
3. Preserve existing behavior.
4. Keep public APIs stable when possible.
5. Improve maintainability.

If a change violates any of these, it must not be merged.

---

# Freeze Rule

Until SirajOS v1 is released:

* No new architecture.
* No parallel implementations.
* No experimental folders.
* No additional pipelines.

All effort must converge toward a single production architecture.
